The paper deals with algorithmic problems related to verification of systems, which is a topic in formal methods and logic (cs.LO). The focus is on graphs with constant treewidth, which is a topic in graph algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also mentions that the control-flow graphs of most programs have constant treewidth, which suggests a connection to programming languages (cs.PL). Additionally, the paper deals with quantitative properties such as mean-payoff and ratio, which are topics in formal languages and automata theory (cs.FL). Finally, the paper presents algorithms for solving these problems, which is a topic in computational complexity (cs.CC).
